<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 19 at 9:10AM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A line of snow showers will affect Portage...southern Trumbull...
Mahoning...Medina...northern Stark...Summit...northeastern Wayne and
southern Lorain Counties Until 1015 AM EDT....
At 910 AM EDT, radar indicated snow showers along a line extending
from near Wellington to near Brunswick to near Hubbard, moving
southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Visibility dropping to less than three quarters of a mile...
Up to 1 inch of quick snow accumulation...
Locations impacted include...
Akron, Canton, Youngstown, Warren, Medina, Salem, Ravenna,
Columbiana, Cuyahoga Falls, Strongsville, Boardman, Brunswick, North
Royalton, Kent, Barberton, Green, Alliance, Hudson, Wadsworth and
Niles.
Use extra caution if you must travel. Rapid changes in visibility and
potentially slick roads may lead to accidents.</description>
